{"word":"βάξις","slug":"βάξις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>βάξις</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:βάζω'><el>βάζω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a saying</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> <i>an oracular saying</i>, like <el>φήμη</el>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a report, rumour</i>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>ἁλώσιμος β.</el> <i>tidings</i> of the capture, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}